{{seealso|2013年巴西抗议运动|2014年巴西抗议运动}}
早在[[2013年联合会杯|2013年联合会杯]]开赛前，就有示威活动在比赛场馆[[巴西利亚国家体育场|巴西利亚国家体育场]]外发生。组织者不满大量资金使用在世界杯的举办中<ref name="Confederations Cup opening protests">{{cite web|title=Brazil Beats Japan, Protests Spoil Confederations Cup Opening Day|url=http://www.voanews.com/content/brazil-japan-confederations-cup/1682679.html|work=[[美国之音|美国之音]]|publisher=[[美国联邦政府|美国联邦政府]]|accessdate=2013-06-16|author=[[路透社|路透社]]|location=[[巴西利亚|巴西利亚]]|date=2013-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518101052/http://www.voanews.com/content/brazil-japan-confederations-cup/1682679.html|archive-date=2015-05-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。将在开幕式上讲话的巴西总统[[迪尔玛·罗塞夫|迪尔玛·罗塞夫]]和国际足联主席布拉特，都遭到民众的嘘声<ref>{{cite web |last=Peck |first=Brooks |url=http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/soccer-dirty-tackle/sepp-blatter-brazil-president-dilma-booed-confederations-cup-201019866.html |title=Sepp Blatter, Brazil president Dilma booed at Confederations Cup opening ceremony |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date=2013-05-29 |accessdate=2013-06-16 |archive-date=2013-06-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619044725/http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/soccer-dirty-tackle/sepp-blatter-brazil-president-dilma-booed-confederations-cup-201019866.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。故[[国际足联|国际足联]]宣布世界杯的开幕式将不会有任何讲话<ref>{{cite web |title=Fifa scraps speeches to avoid protest |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-26539972 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2014-03-12 |accessdate=2014-07-16 |archive-date=2014-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713031528/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-26539972 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。抗议活动还蔓延至联合会杯其他比赛的场外，部分巴西城市爆发对政府财务管理表示失望的暴乱<ref name="Confederations Cup opening protests"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://rt.com/news/brazil-protest-demonstration-unrest-741/ |title=Brazil despair: Protests over transport, inflation gain intl support (PHOTOS) — RT News |publisher=Rt.com |accessdate=2013-06-18 |archive-date=2013-06-26 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HetjArDm?url=http://rt.com/news/brazil-protest-demonstration-unrest-741/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

世界杯前一周及首日，全国各地进一步爆发抗议财政支出的动乱<ref name="World Cup protests1">{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/05/16/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|title=Strikes, violent protests hit Brazil ahead of World Cup|publisher=CNN|date=2014-05-16|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140623134638/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/05/16/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="World Cup protests2">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/06/16/world-cup-2014-17-pictures-of-shocking-violence-police-open-live-fire-anti-fifa-protesters_n_5498351.html|title=17 Pictures Of Shocking Violence As Police 'Open Live Fire' On Anti-Fifa Protesters|publisher=Huffington Post|date=2014-06-16|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618220310/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/06/16/world-cup-2014-17-pictures-of-shocking-violence-police-open-live-fire-anti-fifa-protesters_n_5498351.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="World Cup protests3">{{cite news|title=Brazilian police fire tear gas at World Cup protesters; CNN employees injured by anti-riot weapons|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/12/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|publisher=CNN|date=2014-06-12|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704210719/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/12/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。但与联合会杯相反，安全部队成功防止抗议抵达场馆<ref>{{cite news|title=Has Brazil proved World Cup doubters wrong?|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-27866983|publisher=BBC|date=2014-06-16|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729225541/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-27866983|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

6月12日，[[CNN|CNN]]记者沙斯塔·达林顿和制片人芭芭拉·奥凡尼提迪斯报道抗议时受伤。两人报道防暴武器被滥用时，[[催泪瓦斯|催泪瓦斯]]弹直接打在芭芭拉的手腕上<ref>{{cite news |title=CNN producer left bloodied after trouble breaks out on day one in Brazil |url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/blogs/the-rio-report/cnn-reporters-left-bloodied-trouble-breaks-day-one-135909960.html |date=2014-06-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714210544/https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/blogs/the-rio-report/cnn-reporters-left-bloodied-trouble-breaks-day-one-135909960.html |archivedate=2014-07-14 |accessdate=2014-08-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Brazilian police fire tear gas at World Cup protesters; CNN employees injured by anti-riot weapons|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/12/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|date=2014-06-12|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704210719/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/06/12/world/americas/brazil-world-cup-protests/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sao Paulo violent protests on World Cup opening day as journalist 'injured' amid rubber bullets and stun grenades|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/southamerica/brazil/10895328/Sao-Paulo-violent-protests-on-World-Cup-opening-day-as-journalist-injured-amid-rubber-bullets-and-stun-grenades.html|date=2014-06-12|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2014-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703102905/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/southamerica/brazil/10895328/Sao-Paulo-violent-protests-on-World-Cup-opening-day-as-journalist-injured-amid-rubber-bullets-and-stun-grenades.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同日揭幕战开赛前，圣保罗和里约热内卢等数个城市的警方与示威者爆发冲突。圣保罗警方动用了催泪瓦斯<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-27811657|title=Brazil World Cup: Clashes at Sao Paulo and Rio protests|date=12 June 2014|work=BBC News|accessdate=2014-06-13|archive-date=2014-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140613023706/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-27811657|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/jun/12/anti-world-cup-protests-brazilian-cities-sao-paulo-rio-de-janeiro|title=Anti-World Cup protests in Brazilian cities mark countdown to kick-off|date=2014-06-12|work=卫报|accessdate=2014-06-13|archive-date=2014-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140613044647/http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/jun/12/anti-world-cup-protests-brazilian-cities-sao-paulo-rio-de-janeiro|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2656102/Brazil-gets-ready-greatest-Earth-just-dont-mention-poor-pitches-subway-strikes-protests-hackers.html|title=Brazilian protesters angry at the cost of the World Cup set fires in the streets and clash violently with riot police hours before opening match in Sao Paulo|date=2014-06-12|work=每日邮报|accessdate=2014-06-13|archive-date=2014-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140612131719/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2656102/Brazil-gets-ready-greatest-Earth-just-dont-mention-poor-pitches-subway-strikes-protests-hackers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

布拉特表示，示威者“不应使用足球表达诉求”，而举办赛事的公共开支“不仅关于世界杯项目，更事关未来”。布拉特表示，示威者“不该使用足球来表达自身诉求”，并表示在举办比赛的公众开支上，考虑到的，不仅是世界杯，还有日后的项目<ref name="Blatter">{{cite web |url=http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1480149/protests-continue-brazil?cc=5739# |title=Brazil protests continue |publisher=ESPN |date=2013-06-19 |accessdate=2014-08-17 |archive-date=2013-06-26 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HetvM0fu?url=http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1480149/protests-continue-brazil?cc=5739 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。随后总统罗塞夫在公共广播回应公众，她表示：“联邦政府用在体育场馆的钱是融资得来的，开发这些场馆的公司和政府要适时偿还这些款项<ref name="dailymail1">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2346359/Brazil-president-Dilma-Rousseff-defends-public-spending-World-Cup.html|title=Brazil president Rousseff defends public spending on World Cup as protests continue|date=2013-06-22|publisher=每日邮报|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-date=2013-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623182731/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2346359/Brazil-president-Dilma-Rousseff-defends-public-spending-World-Cup.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

